Use `async`/`await`, keep order the same, and preserve `next(err)`:

```js
async function verifyWebhook(req, res, next) {
  try {
    const signature = req.headers['x-signature'];
    const payload = req.body;

    const isValid = await verifySignature(payload, signature);
    if (!isValid) {
      return res.status(401).send('Invalid signature');
    }

    return next();
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
}
```

Verify:
- middleware order is unchanged
- every async call is awaited
- errors still go to `next(err)`
- no response is sent

